In this, his only film, Freddie really showed his acting chops!! His performance as Muff Kovack was neither over nor under acted. The plot is questionable, but considering the era when it was filmed (the 70s) it is good. The supporting cast was very good.

I STRONGLY RECOMMEND this film as a MUST SEE for anyone who still associate FREDDIE PRINZE SR with his character FRANCISCO "CHICO" RODRIGUEZ.

Freddie Prinze proved in this movie that he could have handled dramatic roles as well.  I read he wasn't happy with this movie but I enjoyed it very much.  The cast was very good too.  I won't give anything away but I do recommend this movie for anyone who hasn't seen Freddie outside Chico and The Man or even the comedy stage.  It is something different and I'd say it's a must for any Freddie Prinze fan.  Highly recommended.

A.M Torres Author of Love Child (sold on Amazon on paperback and kindle)
